fields.name: miraclefeet
fields.org_mission: miraclefeet is dedicated to providing proper treatment for children born with clubfoot in developing countries. miraclefeet partners with local orthopedic surgeons working in public hospitals to establish and support clubfoot clinics within the existing public health system. miraclefeet believes this is the most effective, efficient and sustainable approach to prevent the significant disability caused by untreated clubfoot around the world.

fields.name: Hoffman Solutions
fields.org_mission: Hoffman Solutions aims to provide the very best solutions for projects in Kenya.

fields.name: Kenya Solutions
fields.org_mission: Build a solution to provide Kenyan citizens with easy access to information about public administration and service delivery at the county and constituency levels, as well as the ability to send questions and comments to county and constituency officials responsible for resource mobilization, allocation and management.

fields.name: Cool Planet Labs
fields.org_mission: Hometowns is a community created, community curated, community controlled social connection platform.  Think user-controlled Facebook with deeper place-based integration, promoting local sharing economy and local connection.  Self-sustaining monetization will be controlled from the bottom up (e.g., crowdsourced selection of who can advertise/sponsor), not the top down. Content and privacy will be determined by the users, not by corporate dictate.  Hometowns has a value proposition, a team assembled and relationships with large existing networks including Sierra Club, Transition Towns, etc.  Hometowns' next step is to prototype the technology platform for show and tell with investors and to release to alpha user communities for feedback and iteration.

fields.name: Nsamizi
fields.org_mission: Our mission is to create a sustainable country-wide network of solar technicians able to manufacture, market, sell, install and support locally made solar products.

fields.name: Alliance for Change
fields.org_mission: The mission of the Alliance for CHANGE is to facilitate the healthy and safe reintegration of incarcerated men and women back into society.  We recognize that this requires an active process of re-socialization, including pre-parole and post-parole community support.  Our program incorporates core principles of social justice and community living as well as practical skills that ensure successful reintegration and lifestyle change that is beneficial to the participant as well as his or her larger community.

fields.name: West Oakland Environmental Indicators Project
fields.org_mission: The West Oakland Environmental Indicators Project is a resident led, community-based environmental justice organization dedicated to achieving healthy homes, healthy jobs and healthy neighborhoods for all who live, work, learn and play in West Oakland, California. Our mission is to build grassroots capacity to provide local leadership for positive change.

fields.name: Local Catch
fields.org_mission: Local Catch is a Community Supported Fishery that connects local fisherman to the community. They also provide members with fresh, sustainably caught seafood, while offering  fisherman better value for the fish they catch.

fields.name: Husika Kenya!
fields.short_desc: Inform and empower Kenyan citizens with access to information about public administration and service delivery.
fields.description: In March 2013 the Kenyan government began the process of devolving from a highly centralized structure that included eight provinces and 408 districts to a structure with two levels of government: national and county. Devolution and the formation of 47 semi-autonomous counties is viewed as a way to increase democratic processes and reduce corruption. Existing sources of information about public administration and service delivery focus entirely on the national level. While there are national level sources of information in Kenya, there are not similar sources of information that focus on the new counties, themselves. Picture the difficulties you would have, with very limited access to information about public administration and local service delivery in the place where you live!

fields.name: Local Catch: A Community Supported Fishery
fields.short_desc: Building a community that values fresh, sustainable seafood
fields.description: Local Catch delivers fresh, sustainably caught seafood to members, while also offering fishermen better value for the fish they catch. "[They] believe you can’t get fresher seafood than from your [local bay],  healthy seafood comes from healthy oceans and communities, and investment in conservation and local fishing economy supports sustainable fisheries."
